    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i've noticed something really weird with my smart thermostat. every time i get really stressed or start having an argument, the temp drops like 3-4 degrees instantly. it's not like a programmed schedule or anything. it feels like it's reacting to the vibe in the room. is there any way these things can actually sense human emotions or something?",
